Usage: php slides [command] [options] [..args]

Commands:
  serve                       Run and serve the PhpSlides project in development mode.
  make:controller <name>      Create a route controller class.
  make:api-controller <name>  Create an API controller class.
  make:middleware <name>      Create a middleware class.

Options:
  -h, --help                  Show this help message and exit.
      --strict                Enforce strict class standards for the generated code.

Examples:
  php slides make:controller User --strict
    Creates a route controller class named `User` with strict coding standards.

  php slides make:api-controller Product
    Creates an API controller class named `Product`.

  php slides make:middleware AuthMiddleware
    Creates a middleware class named `AuthMiddleware`.

For more information on each command, use `php slides <command> --help`.
